SE MILITARY CHIEF'S VISIT TO US\n\nGeneral Ne Win, the commander in chief of the Burmese armed forces, was authorized to bring up in Washington the matter of Chinese Nationalist collaboration with the Karen insurgents in his impending talks with American officials. The Karens were trying to buy arms from the Nationalists for direct shipment from Taipei to Burma.\n\nComment\n\nBurma continues to feel that the United States is ultimately responsible for Chinese Nationalist intrigues with Burmese dissident groups.\n\nTaipei for some months has been committed to provide a shipment of arms to the insurgents. The pledge has not yet been carried out, however, principally because of Karen difficulties in arranging for delivery of the arms after Thailand refused to permit their transshipment through its territory", "token_count": 136, "token_end_0based": 135, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "5 taiwan collaboration with karens may be brought up during burmese military chief's visit to us general ne win the commander in chief of the burmese armed forces was authorized to bring up in washington the matter of chinese nationalist collaboration with the karen insurgents in his impending talks with american officials the karens were trying to buy arms from the nationalists for direct shipment from taipei to burma comment burma continues to feel that the united states is ultimately responsible for chinese nationalist intrigues with burmese dissident groups taipei for some months has been committed to provide a shipment of arms to the insurgents the pledge has not yet been carried out however principally because of karen difficulties in arranging for delivery of the arms after thailand refused to permit their transshipment through its territory", "unred_source_page": 8}
